@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title State Machine - nosql/Table
skinparam state {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
}
state "provisioning\nprovider: CREATING" as provisioning
state "active\nprovider: ACTIVE" as active
state "updating" as updating
state "terminating\nprovider: DELETING" as terminating
[*] --> provisioning : CreateTable
provisioning --> active : ACTIVE
active --> updating : ChangeTableCompartment,\nUpdateTable
updating --> active : update targets
active --> terminating : DeleteTable
terminating --> [*] : DELETED
note right of active
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: nosql
slug: table
kind: Table
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update none;
delete DELETING
mutable/forceNew: compartment_id, ddl_statement,
defined_tags, freeform_tags (+4 more) /
is_auto_reclaimable, name
open gaps: bind-versus-create, list-lookup,
mutation-policy, waiter-work-request
Scaffold metadata only; replace with
controller-specific runtime states before
promotion.
end note
@enduml
